        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/6/68",
        "text": [
          " أَمِيرُ اَلْمُؤْمِنِينَ عَلِيٌّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ: «اِفْتِتَاحُ اَلصَّلاَةِ اَلْوُضُوءُ وَ تَحْرِيمُهَا اَلتَّكْبِيرُ وَ تَحْلِيلُهَا اَلتَّسْلِيمُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.68 - The Commander of the Faithful Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as), said:\n\"The initiation of prayer is purification (ablution), its prohibition is the takbir (saying 'Allahu Akbar'), and its permissibility is the Tasleem (saying 'Assalamu Alaikum').\""
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
